Each year, my family usually take a road trip to Louisville, Kentucky. Whenever we come; we’re always looking for great places to eat in the downtown area. Over the last few years this has been one of the few places we stop by to grab a quick bite to eat. Well, this recent trip we decided to stop at this location to take a bite to eat before a party. When my family first walked in the restaurant a young lady at the counter did not even acknowledge us because she and another worker was too busy running their mouth. After a few minutes of standing in line; when there were no customers, she finally took our order. My family took our seats and begin chatting it up with other family members who work in and/or around the area on 4 Street. I start to notice more people coming in ten minutes after my family took our seats; and you can tell they were starting to pick up a little more. Fifteen minutes past after we took our seats and one of the worker’s came over with my sister’s order; which was a Smashburger (lettuce, cheese and tomatoes) with fries.  She begins to eat it. A little more time went on and I realized my food has not come out yet. I look in the back and I see the same young lady who took our order eating back in the kitchen. A young man came over and said my food will be out shortly. Ten more minutes went by and still there was no food I had ordered but somehow all those who ordered after me had received their food. I turned around at my sister to ask her a question; she looks at her burger and squint her eyes. I asked her what was wrong and she took her two fingers and pulls out a long strand of dark hair from between the cheese and burger! Mind you she has bright red hair! We told the worker, he stated he was sorry and said he will make another one for her to go. My food still wasn’t out to my table by this time. I go back up to the register and asked for my money back and the young man who have been dealing with us goes to get the manager; who was looking unconcerned. I spoke to him about how long I’ve been waiting and I will take my money and service elsewhere. He said he was “sorry and didn’t know what was going on and that I had ordered” Mind you he been glancing at me for almost an hour when I was there. My aunt leaned over and the young lady who took our order, eating while fixing the food; looks at my aunt and said she is sorry and she “forgot”; and my sister never got a burger to go! DO NOT go to this location!
